<div class="line-length-m">
  <p>Color palettes give you a full spectrum of colors to use in your project.</p>

  <p>A color palette defines 10 hues — red, orange, yellow, green, cyan, blue, indigo, purple, pink, and gray — each
    with a scale of 11 tints from <code>05</code> (darkest) to <code>95</code> (lightest) available as <a
      href="/docs/tokens/color">color design tokens</a>. While the tints have similar lightness values across palettes,
    each palette has unique hue shifts and chroma so you can find just the right vibe to your project. Combine a palette
    with a <a href="/docs/themes">theme</a> and <a href="/docs/tokens/color#variant-colors">variant colors</a> to style
    the whole library.</p>
</div>

